<Title>i love it, but...
<Date>Thu Oct 27 00:00:00 CST 2005
<Content>Don't get me wrong, I love the Zen Micro, but there are a few problems that everyone should be aware of.    The sound quality is amazing and I love having a ton of  music at my fingertips.  The problem is the fingertips.  The controls take awhile to get used to and they are not the most operator friendly.  I am sometimes frustrated with the way the controls are too sensitive or not sensitive enough.  I usually try to set it to what I want and leave it alone instead of constantly hunting for a different song or album.   Also the software is not the most user friendly.  I had to kind of play with it to figure it out and I am still learning some of the finer points.  Once you get the hang of it it is not too bad, but at first it is frustrating and I don't consider myself computer illiterate.  Overall though, I must say that I love the Zen Micro.  I think it was worth the initial frustration to get to have so much music in such a little package with such good sound quality.  I have about 690 songs and 4 sizeable playlists and I have only used a little over half of my memory.  I would suggest the Zen Micro to anyone who will deal with a little frustration to get the most out of a great device.  
<Overall>4

